div.p:
I remember, that a Gentleman some time ago wrote a description of King's Island for the Tasmanian journals;
The Papers and proceedings of the Royal Society of Tasmania for 1873 includes (p. 50) a brief description of King Island, in Bass Strait, extracted from the Tasmanian Government gazette, 31 March 1827, that may be the report to which M is referring. but I cannot find the copy, which I received; thus some plants may be mentioned in that report, and perhaps the highest points of elevation could be ascertained from the survey-office. Memoranda to that effect would be interesting, if appended to my present notes.
No such annotations were added to M's text.
